ResourceHeader.ResourceName: Pioneer 11 Geiger Tube Telescope (GTT) 15-min count rate data
ResourceHeader.Description:
This data set holds 15-min count rates and related
parameters for each of 8 sensors or multi-sensor coincidence modes,
as obtained from the U.Iowa Geiger Tube Telescope (GTT) experiment flown 
on Pioneer 11.  Single-sensor count rates are from the A (directional 
fluxes of 0.04-21 MeV electrons and 0.61-80 MeV protons, plus omnidirectional 
fluxes of .GT.21 MeV electrons and .GT.80 MeV protons), B (directional fluxes 
of 0.56-21 MeV electrons and 9-80 MeV protons, plus omnidirectional
fluxes of .GT.21 MeV electrons and .GT.80 MeV protons), C (omnidirectional
fluxes of .GT.21 MeV electrons and .GT.80 MeV protons), D (omnidirectional
fluxes of .GT.31 MeV electrons and .GT.80 MeV protons), and G (directional 
fluxes of 0.61-3.41 MeV protons) Geiger tubes.  Coincidence mode rates 
are given for Geiger tube combinations (A,B), (A,B,C) and (D,E,F).  
The G and (A,B,C) rates are each given multiple times in the 12 rates 
of each 15-min record.  Additional parameters associated with each count
rate include numbers of counts contributing to each count rate, the 
statistical uncertainty in each rate, and others used in U. Iowa's
processing and carried along for posterity.  These are described in
the document identified in the first "Information URL."  The data were 
provided to NSSDC on VMS-binary-formatted tapes and were converted to
ASCII by GSFC/SPDF in 2009.  The data are available in 6-month ASCII
files whose sizes range from ~20MB early in the mission to .LT.1MB
late in the mission.

Parameter.Name: Sensor A count rate
Parameter.Description:
Count rate due to directional fluxes of 
0.04-21 MeV electrons and 0.61-80 MeV protons, plus omnidirectional 
fluxes of .GT.21 MeV electrons and .GT.80 MeV protons

Parameter.Name: Sensor B count rate
Parameter.Description:
Count rate due to directional fluxes of 
0.56-21 MeV electrons and 9-80 MeV protons, plus omnidirectional
fluxes of .GT.21 MeV electrons and .GT.80 MeV protons

Parameter.Name: Sensor C count rate
Parameter.Description:
Count rate due to omnidirectional fluxes of 
.GT.21 MeV electrons and .GT.80 MeV protons

Parameter.Name: Sensor D count rate
Parameter.Description:
Count rate due to omnidirectional fluxes of 
.GT.31 MeV electrons and .GT.80 MeV protons

Parameter.Name: Sensor G count rate
Parameter.Description:
Count rate due to directional fluxes of 
0.61-3.41 Mev protons.  See also columns 37 and 44.

Parameter.Name: Coincidence mode (A,B) count rate
Parameter.Description:
(A,B) coincidence mode count rate due to directional fluxes of 
.GT.21 MeV electrons and .GT.130 MeV protons.

Parameter.Name: Coincidence mode (A,B,C) count rate
Parameter.Description:
(A,B,C) coincidence mode count rate due to directional fluxes of 
.GT.21 MeV electrons and .GT.130 MeV protons.  See also columns 42 and 45.

Parameter.Name: Coincidence mode (D,E,F) count rate
Parameter.Description:
(D,E,F) coincidence mode count rate due to omnidirectional 
fluxes of .GT.31 MeV electrons and .GT.150 MeV protons.  E and F are Geiger
tubes whose individual count rates are not taken.

Parameter.Name: Standard deviations in all count rates
Parameter.Description:
Standard deviations [count rate/SQRT(#points)]
in each of the 12 count rates of columns 34-45.

Structure.Description:
Standard deviation in the count rates in Columns 
34 to 45, respectively

Parameter.Name: Numbers of raw counts in all count rates
Parameter.Description:
Number of raw counts in each of the 12 count 
rates in columns 34-45

Structure.Description:
numbers of counts in the count rates in Columns 
34 to 45, respectively

Parameter.Name: Spacecraft position information

Structure.Description: Positional parameters for spacecraft and earth
